  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"single-post\"\u003e\n        \n                \n        \u003cp\u003e\u003cimg fetchpriority=\"high\" width=\"750\" height=\"461\" src=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Museum-of-All-Things-750x461.png\" alt=\"\" decoding=\"async\" srcset=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Museum-of-All-Things-750x461.png 750w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Museum-of-All-Things-1090x670.png 1090w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Museum-of-All-Things-210x129.png 210w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Museum-of-All-Things-768x472.png 768w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Museum-of-All-Things.png 1400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" data-attachment-id=\"77728\" data-permalink=\"https://flowingdata.com/2025/02/27/wikipedia-as-a-walkable-virtual-museum/museum-of-all-things/\" data-orig-file=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Museum-of-All-Things.png\" data-orig-size=\"1400,860\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026#34;aperture\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;credit\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;camera\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;caption\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;created_timestamp\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;copyright\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;focal_length\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;iso\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;shutter_speed\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;title\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;orientation\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;}\" data-image-title=\"Museum of All Things\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Museum-of-All-Things-750x461.png\" data-large-file=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Museum-of-All-Things-1090x670.png\"/\u003e                    \u003c/p\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n                                    \n                \u003cp\u003eImagine everything on Wikipedia in an infinite museum of galleries. \u003ca href=\"https://mayeclair.itch.io/museum-of-all-things\"\u003eThat’s what Maya Claire did\u003c/a\u003e, and you can walk through the museum via your desktop computer or in virtual reality.\u003cbr/\u003e\n\u003cspan id=\"more-77726\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe museum is greatly inspired by \u003ca href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jR0vRuZkxdw\"\u003eeducational videos\u003c/a\u003e that I watched as a kid, and the liminal spaces produced by early CGI. I want to recapture the promise that the internet can be a place of endless learning and exploration. I hope you enjoy your time exploring the Museum of All Things!\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eClaire used the Godot game engine to make MoAT and Blender to model objects. The codebase is available \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/m4ym4y/museum-of-all-things\"\u003eon GitHub\u003c/a\u003e. You can download the museum to your desktop \u003ca href=\"https://mayeclair.itch.io/museum-of-all-things\"\u003efor major operating systems\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNaturally, I went to the data visualization exhibit:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"77732\" data-permalink=\"https://flowingdata.com/2025/02/27/wikipedia-as-a-walkable-virtual-museum/data-visualization-gallery/\" data-orig-file=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/data-visualization-gallery.png\" data-orig-size=\"2786,1789\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026#34;aperture\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;credit\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;camera\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;caption\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;created_timestamp\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;copyright\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;focal_length\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;iso\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;shutter_speed\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;title\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;orientation\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;}\" data-image-title=\"data visualization gallery\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/data-visualization-gallery-750x482.png\" data-large-file=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/data-visualization-gallery-1090x700.png\" src=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/data-visualization-gallery-750x482.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"482\" srcset=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/data-visualization-gallery-750x482.png 750w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/data-visualization-gallery-1090x700.png 1090w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/data-visualization-gallery-210x135.png 210w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/data-visualization-gallery-768x493.png 768w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/data-visualization-gallery-1536x986.png 1536w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/data-visualization-gallery-2048x1315.png 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt’s fun. You start in a lobby and can interact with a search console. After you find what you’re looking for, a hallway opens up in a magical portal sort of way and you can walk around. \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI would’ve stayed longer, but the fan on my old-ish Mac was whirring. I’m curious what the VR experience is like.\u003c/p\u003e\n                \n                \n                                        \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n                    \n 